# Rate Limiting Implementation

## Configuration
Rate limiters are configured in [rateLimiter.ts](mdc:src/server/rateLimiter.ts) using express-rate-limit:

### API Limiter
- Window: 15 minutes
- Max Requests: 100
- Used for: General API endpoints

### Auth Limiter
- Window: 1 hour
- Max Requests: 5
- Used for: Authentication endpoints

### Form Limiter
- Window: 1 hour
- Max Requests: 10
- Used for: Form submission endpoints

### Contentful Limiter
- Window: 1 minute
- Max Requests: 30
- Used for: Contentful API requests

### Health Check Limiter
- Window: 1 minute
- Max Requests: 60
- Used for: Health check endpoints

## Usage
Rate limiters are applied in [middleware.ts](mdc:src/server/middleware.ts) based on route patterns:
- `/api/auth/*` → Auth Limiter
- `/api/forms/*` → Form Limiter
- `/api/content/*` → Contentful Limiter
- `/api/health` → Health Check Limiter
- `/api/*` → General API Limiter

## Testing
Tests in [rateLimiter.test.ts](mdc:src/server/__tests__/rateLimiter.test.ts) verify:
- Requests within limits are allowed
- Requests exceeding limits are blocked
- Appropriate error messages are returned
- Rate limit headers are set correctly
